<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="196" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,295,1221]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,439,465]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Etymology</emphasis>
: The name refer to xrafstra, which are evil, usually nocturnal spirits in Persian mythology that entered the human world, sometimes disguised as wasps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1416,511,538]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,295,1221]" box="[199,1416,511,538]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,511,537]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1905" box="[447,689,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
<emphasis box="[447,689,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Ophion turcomanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with narrower face and fewer teeth on the hind tarsal claws.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,295,1221]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,547,573]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Description</emphasis>
: Male unknown. Fore wing length 
<quantity box="[725,806,547,574]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="45" pageNumber="196" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[957,1038,547,574]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="45" pageNumber="196" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
.Antenna with 44‒45 flagellomeres. Temples in lateral view buccate, about 0.8 × as long as compound eye. Gap between lateral ocelli and inner margin of compound eye wide, about 0.2‒0.3 × the diameter of ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[832,934,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22C</figureCitation>
). Face relatively narrow (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1316,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina centrally evenly rounded. Face below antennal sockets strongly polished with weak very scarce punctures. Malar space about 0.1 × as long as mandibular base. Mandibular gape strongly acute and mandibular teeth very long (
<figureCitation box="[218,322,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
). First flagellomere 4.0 × as long as wide. Central flagellomeres stout, about 1.4‒1.5 × as long as wide. Apical flagellomeres approximately 1.6 × as long as wide. Mesoscutum strongly polished with quite dense, but very weak and irregular punctuation. Mesopleuron polished with very weak punctures, space between punctures about two × their diameter. Epicnemial carina, in antero-ventral view, with pleurosternal angles strongly obtuse and indistinct, distinctly anterior to sternal angles. Scutellum without lateral carinae. Propodeum quite polished with only the anterior transverse carina distinct throughout its length. Posterior transverse carina widely interrupted centrally (
<figureCitation box="[160,262,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22B</figureCitation>
). Two short parallel carinae present centrally at the indicated junction with the posterior transverse carina. Sclerotised part of first sternite ending level to spiracle. Hind trochantellus shorter than wide in dorsal view. Hind femur about 6.0 × as long as wide. Inner spur of hind tibia about 0.3 × as long as hind metatarsus, outer spur 0.6 × as long as outer spur. Hind tarsal claws with about six spines with quite large insterstices (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1232,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
). Wing membrane clear. Ramellus reaching 0.2 × the width of the discosubmarginal cell. Radius weakly sinuous in outer part, straight before junction with pterostigma. Nervellus broken in the middle or slightly below the middle by the discoidella.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,295,1221]" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis box="[199,336,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Colouration</emphasis>
: Body pale yellowish with typical coloration of desert species (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1214,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 22. Ophion xrafstra Johansson sp. nov. holotype ♀ (HMIM). A) habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) hind tarsal claws; E) head, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225702/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="196">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
). Mandibular teeth black.
</paragraph>
